Amazing atmosphere! This is by far the best breakfast/brunch place in Honolulu! They are always consistent. The food is amazing whether you like sweet or savory. The pancake souffle options are all amazing, my personal favorites are the blueberry souffle and the banana souffle. The customer service is excellent and the interior and outdoor exterior is decorated so intricately. There is always a fresh tiny flower on every table. Not only is the presentation of the food absolutely beautiful but it always tastes delicious. It is located at the bottom of the Monarch Hotel and there is parking in the building that is free with validation. By far the best breakfast place ever!
Loved the French toast and souffle pancakes.
Going again for breakfast it is THAT good.

Atmosphere was really great. Long wait to get a table, long wait to place order, and really long wait for your food. Service was great but just have to wait a long time for everything. Food was awesome when it finally came but by then I was ready to go. Oh and no photos, weird given the owners are Japanese and it is common place to take photos of your experience to share with others. 7 people and the bill was $166 which is pretty cheap but the coffee is very overpriced here.
French toast is 5. Souffle was cold and bland 3.Atmosphere 5
Really good! Awesome, the should improved the kitchen, they take a litle longer to get our plates
The food was amazing, and the service was great. Very reasonably priced for such delicious and well presented food. A real culinary treat for breakfast, and the best we’ve had on the island so far.

Really outstanding. Top tier service in a quaint and adorable setting. Everything on the menu is great (a cool mix of French and Japanese) -- exactly what I'm looking for in brunch. New outdoor seats as well; very comfy. This place can get busy, so if you go at popular times you'll have to wait.

This is a nice cozy place to have breakfast. First time in Honolulu and the front desk in the hotel recommended it. Their Benedict eggs is another thing, keep in mind they serve small portions. The staff and my waiter was so nice and friendly.
This could possibly be the best breakfast restaurant on the planet. Not even joking.

The service was beyond horrible. While I watched every other table be asked if they were okay four times over before my table being asked anything, after having to raise our hand like a bunch of school children. On top of that the food was flavorless at best, not even worth the plate the food is on. To add insult to injury they couldn't even get our order right, I only ate what they gave me because it took 1 HOUR AND 15 MINUTES TO GET ME A CREPE. They also asked us if we were okay twice the whole time. Absolutely terrible, everything about this place. Thinking if making it a photo op? Don't count on it, you need special permission for that as well. Don't waste your time, go to Mc Donald's.
Absolutely best breakfast in Honolulu ✨

Passed the entrance twice because it's a garden arch with stepping stones. Feels like a 5 star restaurant in the Shire. Very cool decor, staff was extremely polite and helpful and souffle pancakes are amazing. Will definitely return with friends to share the experience.
I would move just to eat breakfast here every morning

The food was great but the wait was long.  Killer French toast.  They could up their covid protocol... Otherwise it would have been 5 star.  Tip, If you rearrange your seating you could fit more customers too.

Lovely cafe...friendly staff! no kids menu listed but they made a great breakfast for our little daughter (Photo) and even sliced cherry tomatoes into little slices for her. food is delicious, variety of choices, from souffle pancakes to maguro rice. highly recommend for bfast 5star++++ thank you guys for having us!
Such a cute and quaint little place! I had the soufflé pancakes and they were divine! A little pricey, but 100% worth it!!
Amazing 👏 the food reminds me of Paris..
Loved this place! The soufflé pancakes are insanely delicious and the people working here are the sweetest! Highly recommend for a lux breakfast/brunch experience!
Very nice interior, photos are prohibited (but got to snuck some), food are alright, 2 cute dogs roam around sometimes

You guys this place is no joke! Not only does it have a super cute and quaint atmosphere and the most wonderful service but the food is to die for! This will be a must stop on every trip going forward!

Wow! From the moment you enter this beautifully decorated cottage style cafe, you will see lush landscaping with a variety of flora.  Once inside, the staff is very attentive and the brunch items are both delicious and visually appealing.  This will be first on my list for breakfast whenever I'm fortunate to be on Oahu.  Owners are very gracious and help the staff whenever needed.
Eggs benedict with Ahi were amazing! Souffle crepe just melted in my mouth!

Awesome breakfast! Best eggs Benedict I have ever had (I ordered the Hawaiian version). My wife got the pancakes which were the fluffy Japanese version, very good. Place is extremely well run by a friendly Japanese staff that worked hard and very quickly! Only downside is it’s a little expensive for some eggs and pancakes (and two juices) ran for about $70 (and I’m from New York where everything is pricey) but I guess it’s ok to pay for high quality and nice/efficient staff. Would be back!
Tried the omelette and Soufflé pancakes and loved both. Didn’t feel too heavy after eating here which is always nice. Super cute ambience too
Delicious
Amazing service

Don’t let me pictures fool you it’s a cool setup inside and outside but not worth the wait/price. My drink came out immediately but my girlfriend waited 15 minutes and finally asked for hers. You have to pay $1 extra for no ice which I can understand but the orange juice was probably 3/4 full so that was disappointing. My food came out first and my girlfriend had to wait another 5 minutes after I got my food so by the time we started eating my pancakes weren’t warm anymore. The French toast were actually good but the pancakes were barely ok. We ordered a side of bacon and potatoes and the bacon was not good and the potatoes were ok but cold. Definitely not worth the wait or price I wouldn’t come back.
Beautiful  restaurant, the service was great and the food is one of  best I have tried so far in 3 years living  in Oahu.

The atmosphere and staff at this restaurant are welcoming and pleasant. The food is delicious and beautifully plated. I definitely enjoyed having breakfast here during my time in Honolulu. I would highly recommend this restaurant to anyone visiting Hawaii for the first time!
a very high in demand place. attention to detail was really good in decor and the staff was beyond nice
Waited over an hour and ended up asking to just pay for our drinks and leave only for them to whip it out last min and my pancakes were sooo undercooked and wet I was so excited for em too

Extremely disorganized. There is no rhyme or reason to how people are seated.  Prepare to wait 30 mins in line in front of their cafe for a table only for the person seating tables to forget that you exist and give someone who is just walking in your table.

Cream pot! This is very cute cozy brunch place! Its perfect for ypur weekday or weekend lunch! I had couple plates with friends and their eggs benedict was on the another level. I highly recommend this place if you are new to hawaii and i saw the store owner cleaning the door handles and wondows, which made me safe to dine in this beautiful place!! 👍😉
The waitress took my friend’s order wrong and would not admit it. She blamed us. :(
It's very small and popular so prepare to wait.
Amazing place to eat, food was soooo good. Recommend you go with friends so that you can try as much of the food as possible. The decor was also so stunning and truly can't wait to go back!

Extremely long story but very disappointed.  After about a 30 minute wait in line outside, we were finally seated. We said we didn’t mind being outside but that was before the sun was fully risen; so we both we’re sweating in our seats early on (no coverings)  We got our menus and waters relatively quick. We looked them over... for about 10 minutes untill a server came back over to take our order. I asked what certain things were and he explained them. I ordered something (blueberry fluffy pancake) and then changed my mind when I realized I could get the sauce (caramel) on the side since I’m not a fan of it, but I wanted the bananas (banana fluffy pancake). We also ordered the (strawberry fluffy pancake) and teas. And then we ordered a potato side (there are 2) since the pancakes didn’t look too big in size. Waiter never told us one wasn’t available.  So our food comes out a bit later and he never scratched off the blueberry one so we had 3 pancakes come out, but luckily the runner took the blueberry one back with no issue. I look down and the caramel sauce is all around the edges of the the plate, covering my bananas... but the runner was already gone.  Also, the potato side we ordered came out with the hash-brown version, when we asked for the seasoned potatoes.  No one came over to ask us how our food was, except for a busser walking by with her hands full, asking if we were alright. Time went by and i was really hungry at this point, so I ate the pancake, but no fruit. The potatoes were not what we ordered, nor did we like them or eat them. I couldn’t even eat half of my $16.50 dish.  We stopped the same busser again as she refilled our water and told her that our orders were incorrect. She said ok let me go tell your waiter. She Never came back and our waiter didn’t come out. 20 minutes AFTER we put our forks down, the waiter comes over with the check. We told him the issues with our food and he told us they didn’t have the potatoes we ordered... uh ok (well if we knew that, we wouldn’t have ordered any?) He realized he messed up with the caramel and took it off our bill. We tipped generously even though we were there for TWO HOURS and our orders were wrong. We waited a while for most of the services.. ie. bring us our bill, check in on us, and to correct our dishes.  Overall poor customer service, no shade on the patio, and the food was just ‘ok’. Most likely won’t ever go again, especially if there is a line. It just is not worth it.  Gave two stars for the pancakes being alright (it was my first time with soufflé pancakes and It was very egg-y which was odd tasting but explains the fluff)
Amazing food
We really enjoyed the delectable offerings. The wait was long and they seem to be shorthanded. If you have a few hours to enjoy the fun interior and food,  it is definately worth it.
The cake is good; you can park in the hotel parking and got validated parking by the restaurant $3/hour. Nice decorations.
This little quaint place is a bit of a hidden gem. Friendly & attentive staff and delicious food in a fantastic setting (with indoor and outdoor seating options). I'll be back!

Ok, hidden gem of Oahu and Hawaii. Such a cute place. Plenty of public parking in the hotel. Service with a smile. The food is to die for and worth the Waikiki price. Pet friendly and such a good view of the Ala Wai, we don't like the Ala Wai..., but it was actually nice with the jazz music and cozy atmosphere.
BEST OMLETTE OF MY LIFE. adorable location and the worlds nicest staff. MUST GO

I love this place. The customer service was excellent and the food came speedily. It was very filling and I enjoyed my food very much. I will definitely be coming to this place again. Love it here !!!!
The restaurant is beautiful and detailed. They put a lot of care into everything.  The food was delicious. I would highly recommend!

Perfect, every detail. French omelette perfectly cooked, flavorful, savory. Smooth black coffee. Fantastic service catering to special requests. Very attentive service, coffee refills immediately. Great with covid mask compliance and cleaning too! Loved it 😍

1. People who came after us, were served before us. We had to look for a waiter. 2. The server, who finally took our order was chasing his dog all over the place instead of bringing us water. 3. He brought my coffee 20 mins ago and  my wife’s mango shake is still not here. The place is half empty.

This place is so nice and posh and should be rated higher to be honest. The food was delicious and unique. Its not too sweet and perfect portions. We had the souffle pancakes with strawberries and hawaiian eggs benedict. The service was welcoming, warm and informative. The decor was so so nice. Its a place that leaves you feeling happy.
Service is awesome. The owners are so kind and take good care of you. Souffle pancakes are dank. French toast with bacon was amazing!
Nice place, good breakfast. A bit expensive
Excellent breakfast food options, and they're open until the early afternoon. A must for staying in Waikiki! By far the best pancakes and omelette I've ever eaten.
Very cute cafe with delicious brunch food💕 the people working there were also very nice, def worth going
The best soufflé pancakes of Hawaii! Matching the quality and taste I usually get in Japan! The place is also carefully decorated with care and attention to details. Love it!

The food and coffee was supppperrrrr yummy. I got the raspberry soufflé pancake and the signature mocha. The food is just right and not too sweet. The service was good too!! Would 100% recommend coming here if in the area again. Also the decorations of the place make the place feel very cozy and cute.It also is right next to the canal meaning you will have a nice view since one side of the cafe is mostly windows!!
